<page_title>The Relationship between Interaction Strength and Melting Point</page_title>
<text>The Relationship between Interaction Strength and Melting Point

    

     
You can change the Interaction Strength (the potential well depth parameter Epsilon). At a given temperature, increasing Epsilon will result in condensation, and decreasing Epsilon will lead to  melting. Through this activity, student should learn that for crystals, higher melting temperature is a result of stronger bonding among atoms.

   What does a heat bath mean?
   What are periodic boundary conditions?

</text>
